## Limitations

This report is based on data and analyses available up to October 2023. The complexity of the Brexit vote means that motivations can vary widely among individuals, and not all perspectives may be fully captured. Additionally, the evolving political and economic landscape may influence retrospective interpretations of the reasons behind the vote. Further research could provide more nuanced insights into the long-term impacts of these motivations.

